Sixty-ninth Legislative Assembly of North Dakota
In Regular Session Commencing Tuesday, January 7, 2025
HOUSE BILL NO. 1403
(Representatives Schneider, Brandenburg, Grueneich, D. Johnston, Klemin, Pyle, Davis, Hager)
(Senators Castaneda, Clemens, Dever, Marcellais)
AN ACT to create and enact a new section to chapter 1-03 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating
to the designation of Prisoner of War and Missing in Action Day as a state holiday.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 1-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
enacted as follows:
Prisoner of War and Missing in Action Day.
The third Friday in September of each year is Prisoner of War and Missing in Action Day. To
remember and honor the sacrifices of those who were held captive and returned, as well as those who
remain missing, the governor shall issue a proclamation each year designating the third Friday in
September as Prisoner of War and Missing in Action Day, a state holiday. This section may not be
interpreted to make Prisoner of War and Missing in Action Day a day on which schools and other
entities are required to close.

